				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/the-great-hippo" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3938622); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=3938622&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610183474" alt="The Great Hippo" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=3938622)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/the-great-hippo" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3938622); return false;" >The Great Hippo</a></span> <span class="odate time_1527465867 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">28 May 2018 00:04</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3815291">
									

<p>I'm loathe to say that people shouldn't do a thing just because it's already been done before, but I'm prone to agree &#8212; character-jokes like dado work best in small doses. And the more we learn about dado, the less fun dado becomes.</p>
<p>Indiana Jones is a cool hat Harrison Ford wears while he punches Nazis. Dado is a broken keyboard someone types on while they produce magic pills based on hilarious misunderstandings. Both of these ideas operate on a 'less-is-more' principle: Exploring them too deeply risks destroying the magic and the charm.</p>
<p><strong>ETA:</strong> Not to say this article is bad, or the tipping point; I don't honestly know? But I definitely feel like the tipping point is approaching.</p>

